WEBVTT

00:05.760 --> 00:07.560
This is car 53, accident center.

00:07.680 --> 00:10.000
We're at the scene of the accident.
Bus with truck,

00:10.240 --> 00:12.800
one mile north of 1-10
about 15 seriously injured.

00:12.960 --> 00:14.720
Age 15 to 18.

00:15.440 --> 00:16.680
Car 210 at Angel's headquarters.

00:16.880 --> 00:18.960
Car 210 at Angel's headquarters.
Angels, please come.

00:20.320 --> 00:22.280
Reply.
You are the Angels headquarters.

00:24.360 --> 00:26.600
Angel's headquarters here.
Do you speak.

00:26.720 --> 00:29.240
Angels, we're in a
bus and truck accident.

00:29.360 --> 00:31.760
A high school soccer team.
Patient report is coming soon.

00:31.880 --> 00:33.520
Did you say a school bus?

00:33.920 --> 00:35.720
Correctly.
A school bus-truck collision.

00:35.840 --> 00:38.760
I already have two dead.
No, three.

00:38.880 --> 00:41.360
Three dead.  15 seriously injured.

00:43.760 --> 00:46.400
-Lots of kids.
-Angels, I have 12 cars.

00:46.520 --> 00:47.920
-12 cars are going...
-Getting started soon.

00:48.040 --> 00:50.880
... clear for transport.  The
first wave will come in 5 minutes.

00:51.000 --> 00:51.960
I repeat, five minutes.

00:58.320 --> 00:59.840
You have to wake up, Mike.

01:01.160 --> 01:02.120
OK?

01:02.960 --> 01:06.840
You have to...
you have to open your eyes.

01:08.840 --> 01:09.920
Now.

01:11.360 --> 01:12.480
Please wake up

01:15.320 --> 01:17.840
Yes exactly.  Once again!
Move your hand again!

01:19.280 --> 01:21.040
-What's happening?
-He moves.

01:21.240 --> 01:24.720
His hand moved.
Just a little, but still.

01:25.120 --> 01:26.080
That's great...

01:26.200 --> 01:27.640
It could be... great.

01:27.760 --> 01:28.880
-Could?
-Yes.

01:29.960 --> 01:32.600
-These are just involuntary...
-Mario...

01:32.720 --> 01:34.440
Involuntary movements
and twitching are normal.

01:34.560 --> 01:35.640
He responded to me

01:36.120 --> 01:38.160
I asked him to wake up and
he moved his hand.  I know it.

01:38.280 --> 01:39.240
Then that's a good sign.

01:40.040 --> 01:41.000
Right?

01:41.680 --> 01:42.640
Right.

01:46.640 --> 01:47.600
Are you ready?

01:48.680 --> 01:49.640
Yes.

01:50.240 --> 01:51.640
All hands to the Center Stage.

01:52.160 --> 01:53.760
All hands to the Center Stage.

02:01.560 --> 02:03.920
Seventeen year old with blunt
chest and stomach injuries.

02:04.040 --> 02:05.760
Pulseless at the scene of the accident.
The pulse came back on the way.

02:05.880 --> 02:07.560
-Now he's gone again.
- Forty-two year old

02:07.680 --> 02:10.120
Belted driver, grazes and
bruises, half unconscious.

02:10.240 --> 02:12.120
We need a head scan
as soon as we arrive, go!

02:12.240 --> 02:13.480
He is passed out,
the pulse is weak.

02:13.600 --> 02:16.080
Positive PSI, facial
trauma, no more signs of life.

02:16.200 --> 02:17.360
He's been lifeless for 20 minutes.

02:17.480 --> 02:18.440
Well, let's get him in.

02:18.560 --> 02:19.520
What's your name?

02:19.640 --> 02:20.640
Holden.

02:20.760 --> 02:22.320
Look at me!  Can you hear me?

02:22.840 --> 02:25.080
We're at the Angels
Memorial, we'll take care of you.

02:25.200 --> 02:26.880
-I'm fine!
-Strong boy!

02:27.760 --> 02:28.720
Is that the bus driver?

02:28.840 --> 02:31.040
No, he died on the spot.
This is the truck driver.

02:31.400 --> 02:32.720
He was heading straight into her lane.

02:32.840 --> 02:35.280
-Saturation is down to 80%.
-Is there a problem, Dr.  Pineda?

02:35.400 --> 02:37.040
No.  But we should
do a tox screen.

02:37.280 --> 02:40.240
How he came from is not
our problem at the moment.

02:40.360 --> 02:41.880
Concentration.
You're not there yet.

02:42.080 --> 02:43.040
Go away.  We have to go through.

02:45.000 --> 02:47.320
James hold on man!

02:47.440 --> 02:48.640
Focus on me.

02:48.760 --> 02:50.080
-OK?
-Will he die?

02:50.200 --> 02:52.000
He has to get on the couch.
He's having a heart attack!

02:52.400 --> 02:53.440
Moment!

02:53.560 --> 02:55.520
The board is stuck on the belt.
Get some scissors!

02:55.640 --> 02:56.640
Don't stop the heart massage!

02:56.760 --> 02:58.000
-Jesse, we need help here.
-James?

02:58.120 --> 02:59.920
James, what are they doing to him?

03:00.560 --> 03:02.960
-Thank you.
-Good.  Two three...

03:04.000 --> 03:05.720
I straighten my leg again.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.880
Dr.  Piel, 10 mg of morphine.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.120
It has been dislocated
before, do it without anesthesia.

03:10.240 --> 03:11.200
Fine

03:11.320 --> 03:12.720
We're at 64%.

03:12.840 --> 03:14.080
It will collapse if it
drops any further.

03:14.200 --> 03:15.520
Sixty-four percent!  What?

03:16.600 --> 03:18.760
So fast  I can't
get the tube in.

03:18.880 --> 03:19.840
Well, away there, away there.

03:19.960 --> 03:21.320
Intubate him, I'll
leave that to you.

03:21.440 --> 03:23.480
Elliot, do the chest
compressions.

03:30.280 --> 03:31.760
What are you doing?
Why are you stopping

03:32.440 --> 03:35.320
There is brain matter
coming out of his ear.

03:35.880 --> 03:38.560
What?  Damn it.

03:39.160 --> 03:40.680
I declare him dead.
Are there any objections?

03:41.920 --> 03:43.960
Time of death is 5:07 pm.

03:44.120 --> 03:46.480
You got six seconds to process

03:47.280 --> 03:48.480
then you come out
of there with me.

03:48.600 --> 03:50.640
James hold on man!

03:53.000 --> 03:54.080
Your coach, I need a room!

03:54.200 --> 03:55.760
Put it here.  This is your room.

03:55.880 --> 03:57.440
Somebody has to
help me find my son!

03:57.560 --> 03:59.480
Sir, you have to stay here.

03:59.600 --> 04:00.720
He is the team captain.

04:02.400 --> 04:03.360
Ready?  Wait a minute.

04:03.480 --> 04:05.320
And one, two...

04:07.400 --> 04:09.080
Sure you don't want
anything that relaxes you?

04:09.480 --> 04:10.440
No.

04:10.840 --> 04:12.440
Give him half the dose.

04:12.560 --> 04:13.840
You put it away well.

04:15.200 --> 04:16.480
Deep breaths.

04:16.600 --> 04:17.560
Come on.

04:17.680 --> 04:18.760
OK.

04:18.880 --> 04:20.680
-Where is the saturation?
-At 50%.

04:20.800 --> 04:23.440
Dr.  Pineda, do the
puncture, please.

04:23.560 --> 04:26.280
Pierce the windpipe.  I agree.

04:26.560 --> 04:28.160
I have it.  I am in.

04:30.440 --> 04:32.400
Don't stop the massage,
not even for a second.

04:32.720 --> 04:36.440
You have to help her!
James hold on man!

04:36.560 --> 04:38.360
Will he get well again?  James!

04:44.720 --> 04:46.040
Dr.  Piel, push him out.

04:46.160 --> 04:48.080
Check the blood
supply to the leg.  Is the?

04:48.200 --> 04:49.160
Count me in!

04:52.040 --> 04:54.040
-How many units are there?
-Four.

04:55.200 --> 04:56.160
Is he alright?

04:58.240 --> 04:59.760
You transfuse the bed, not him.

05:07.880 --> 05:10.160
There are dozens more
kids, declare him dead.

05:10.680 --> 05:11.920
This is not your
patient, doctor.

05:12.240 --> 05:13.920
Tell me what's up

05:14.680 --> 05:16.360
James!  What is happening to him?

05:16.720 --> 05:17.720
Get him out.

05:18.040 --> 05:21.960
James!  What is happening to him?
Is he dead?

05:22.080 --> 05:23.920
James!

05:25.760 --> 05:28.600
Pause chest compressions.
Check the pulse.

05:29.560 --> 05:30.960
Still no pulse.

05:31.760 --> 05:33.720
-Since when has the heart stood still?
-30 minutes.

05:35.320 --> 05:36.600
Someone else is coming!

05:37.240 --> 05:38.200
Put it down somewhere.

05:38.560 --> 05:40.000
Are there any objections?

05:40.680 --> 05:41.640
No.

05:41.800 --> 05:43.160
Four cars are on the way.

05:54.200 --> 05:55.520
I'm sorry kid

05:55.960 --> 05:57.600
I wanted to help him.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.680
I used my jacket as
a pressure bandage.

06:02.720 --> 06:03.960
He's in cardiac arrest.

06:05.280 --> 06:06.480
I wanted to help him.

06:07.000 --> 06:08.320
I am the team captain.

06:08.560 --> 06:09.600
I'm sorry kid

06:09.720 --> 06:10.680
We can't identify any.

06:10.800 --> 06:11.760
Everyone is wearing
their jerseys and their

06:11.880 --> 06:13.640
IDs are in their sports
bags under the bus.

06:26.400 --> 06:27.680
Do you know where my dad is?

06:28.840 --> 06:30.400
Nobody knows where he is.

06:31.280 --> 06:33.760
I think he's fine.
I saw him go away.

06:35.360 --> 06:38.520
It's you, Jessamine, isn't it?

06:39.120 --> 06:41.520
I mean, Charlotte Piel.

06:42.920 --> 06:44.360
I read that you became a doctor.

06:46.360 --> 06:47.720
It still hurts.

06:49.440 --> 06:50.560
Mom right?

06:51.080 --> 06:52.880
-That works too.
-Could you help me out here?

06:53.280 --> 06:54.480
That's what I'm here for.

06:54.840 --> 06:55.800
OK.

06:56.360 --> 06:58.160
He says he's in great pain.

06:58.600 --> 07:00.040
You put your knee
back into place, right?

07:01.720 --> 07:03.400
What?  What's happening?

07:04.040 --> 07:05.160
Dr.  Willis...

07:05.600 --> 07:07.160
Do you have to consult him?

07:07.440 --> 07:08.640
What's happening?

07:09.280 --> 07:11.040
His pulse values
​​were normal earlier.

07:13.200 --> 07:15.360
-It's like it's on fire.
-No pulse.

07:15.880 --> 07:17.240
I give him five
units of morphine.

07:17.360 --> 07:18.440
I do not get it.

07:18.560 --> 07:20.480
-You should check your pulse.
-I have.  Twice.

07:20.600 --> 07:22.960
The capillary fill time was short.
His pulse was strong.

07:23.080 --> 07:24.040
Not any longer longer.

07:24.160 --> 07:25.920
Does someone want to
tell me what's going on?

07:26.040 --> 07:28.000
-He needs an operation.
-Operated?

07:28.360 --> 07:29.320
How so?

07:29.440 --> 07:31.560
The artery in the back knee
was injured during straightening.

07:31.680 --> 07:33.240
We'll take you to the
operating room to fix that.

07:33.360 --> 07:34.320
OK.

07:34.440 --> 07:36.560
-I'll let the operating room know.
-Good thank you.

07:36.840 --> 07:39.520
Sister, prepare him for
the relocation.  Come.

07:42.080 --> 07:44.160
-Will he lose his leg?
-Why are you here?

07:44.600 --> 07:45.440
Excuse me?

07:45.640 --> 07:47.760
If that's just a stopover
until the next film...

07:47.880 --> 07:49.880
No, I am here to treat patients.

07:50.400 --> 07:52.840
Answer me my question,
is the boy losing his leg?

07:53.040 --> 07:54.560
-Dr.  Willis, is there a problem?
-I'm okay.

07:54.680 --> 07:57.680
I was supposed to be checking
a patient's blood flow, I did.

07:57.800 --> 07:58.920
How exactly?

07:59.040 --> 08:00.240
I checked his pulse.

08:00.360 --> 08:03.800
Dorsalis pedis and tibialis
posterior.  Like in a textbook.

08:03.920 --> 08:06.040
-What textbook is that?
-Elford and Patreedus.

08:06.160 --> 08:07.120
Sorry?

08:07.240 --> 08:08.600
Emergency procedures,
Elford and Patreedus.

08:08.720 --> 08:11.200
I know the book, where
does it say that an artery

08:11.320 --> 08:12.520
injury can only be checked
by measuring your pulse?

08:12.960 --> 08:15.040
Chapter 26, second paragraph.

08:15.320 --> 08:17.640
Ninety percent of all
patients with arterial

08:17.760 --> 08:18.920
injuries show up
on the pulse check.

08:19.080 --> 08:21.040
-Do you remember that?
-But it's not a textbook.

08:22.440 --> 08:25.240
This is a real hospital, 10%
missing, that's too much.

08:25.560 --> 08:27.440
You should have ordered a
Doppler or ankle-arm index.

08:27.640 --> 08:29.240
What is the prognosis
for this patient?

08:29.520 --> 08:30.720
Maybe we were quick enough.

08:30.880 --> 08:32.159
It was my fault, wasn't it?

08:32.640 --> 08:34.200
This boy is losing
his leg because of me.

08:34.320 --> 08:35.280
No, it's not your fault.

08:35.720 --> 08:38.000
Doctor, go to the
patient and write the file.

08:38.840 --> 08:40.440
I want to tell you
something about this girl.

08:40.720 --> 08:42.240
She is the best
of her senior year.

08:42.360 --> 08:45.000
It wasn't her film
career, it was herself.

08:45.160 --> 08:48.600
She is brilliant and
has a good heart.

08:48.720 --> 08:50.120
Maybe I'm used to
military regulations.

08:50.240 --> 08:51.360
She's not in the military.

08:51.640 --> 08:53.520
She is a junior doctor
in her first year, she is

08:53.640 --> 08:57.400
not yet ready for the
consequences of this mistake.

08:59.200 --> 09:00.440
This is none of us.

09:09.320 --> 09:10.600
The police have to go.

09:11.120 --> 09:13.680
-Mrs.  Williams, according to the rules...
-He's passed out!

09:13.800 --> 09:16.000
Why can't you leave him alone?

09:16.400 --> 09:18.080
Officer, please
give us a moment.

09:18.200 --> 09:20.960
You blame him.
You don't know what happened.

09:21.080 --> 09:22.400
They want to find out.

09:22.520 --> 09:24.840
How do they know that the
bus driver is not to blame?

09:24.960 --> 09:26.760
Because the bus
was still in its lane.

09:27.400 --> 09:29.960
Dr.  Pineda, see if there
are beds on the ITS.

09:33.440 --> 09:34.600
He must have fallen asleep.

09:34.720 --> 09:36.480
-He comes to the ITS.
-Is that a crime?

09:36.600 --> 09:38.840
-Maybe a few weeks.
-He always stays awake.

09:38.960 --> 09:40.720
-There is no treatment.
-He rolls down the window

09:40.840 --> 09:42.800
listens to music,
he calls me at home.

09:43.000 --> 09:46.400
He'd never do drugs,
but that's what they think?

09:46.520 --> 09:49.320
The toxicological investigation
will show all of that.

09:49.440 --> 09:50.720
-I'm telling you...
-He'll need you.

09:50.840 --> 09:54.560
My husband is not a criminal.
He follows the rules.

09:54.680 --> 09:56.680
He works so hard.

09:56.800 --> 09:58.720
He couldn't stand
it if he knew he

09:58.840 --> 10:00.560
was responsible for
the death of people.

10:00.680 --> 10:02.120
Because he's a good person.

10:02.480 --> 10:05.360
He is a good man.
Come on, tell him that.

10:05.480 --> 10:07.720
Tell him he's a good man.

10:09.360 --> 10:10.640
At the moment

10:11.000 --> 10:13.920
we have to hope that
the swelling will go down.

10:15.760 --> 10:17.240
What are you saying?

10:19.120 --> 10:20.520
Will he die?

10:21.640 --> 10:23.440
We'll know in a few hours.

10:30.200 --> 10:32.960
Why are we repairing the artery
with tissue from the great rose vein?

10:33.080 --> 10:34.680
You mean why are
you fixing the artery?

10:34.800 --> 10:36.480
I've been holding a
retractor for two hours.

10:36.680 --> 10:38.040
-Are you bored?
-Yes.

10:38.160 --> 10:40.640
Am i a surgeon or a nurse?
No offense.

10:40.920 --> 10:42.040
The jury is still undecided.

10:42.160 --> 10:44.280
Why don't you answer
the question?  If you can.

10:44.400 --> 10:46.760
Better long-term patency
compared to synthetic.

10:46.880 --> 10:48.280
Go on.  I am good at it.

10:48.400 --> 10:50.040
When you're good at it, seal

10:50.160 --> 10:51.400
the distal end of
the anastomosis.

10:52.040 --> 10:53.720
Count to five.

10:54.400 --> 10:57.760
Four, three, two...

10:58.680 --> 11:00.600
-Finished.
-OK.

11:00.720 --> 11:02.080
Let's see what we have here.

11:03.360 --> 11:06.360
No leak.
Distal blood flow is good.

11:07.640 --> 11:08.680
Not good enough.

11:10.160 --> 11:12.800
The tissue does not perfuse.
Damn it.

11:12.920 --> 11:14.560
-It could still...
-No, no.

11:14.680 --> 11:16.880
It's not your fault.
It was too late.

11:17.760 --> 11:19.880
The blood flows in
the foot, but it doesn't

11:20.000 --> 11:22.360
matter, the lower leg
is lost, it is not viable.

11:23.880 --> 11:26.400
We're going to
amputate below the knee.

11:26.920 --> 11:30.480
We have less than
six hours to do it.

11:31.680 --> 11:35.960
He is only 16, his father
has to consent.  Close.

11:39.560 --> 11:41.440
Is it just the lower abdomen?

11:41.560 --> 11:43.520
Yeah, like bad stomach cramps.

11:43.760 --> 11:45.000
How long have you had it?

11:45.160 --> 11:46.400
For at least a month.

11:47.400 --> 11:50.440
I am tough and have
a high pain tolerance.

11:50.880 --> 11:52.280
She is really strong.

11:52.720 --> 11:55.320
There is nothing strong
about ignoring this pain.

11:55.440 --> 11:57.840
It could be an ovarian
cyst or appendicitis.

11:58.320 --> 12:01.000
She needs a urinalysis,
SS test and gyn examination.

12:01.120 --> 12:03.640
-All right, Sugar Bear?
-Yes.  And don't call me that.

12:05.360 --> 12:08.480
We don't have a
hanger here so do this...

12:08.600 --> 12:11.040
... among your... well...

12:11.560 --> 12:12.840
... Po.

12:14.480 --> 12:17.080
-What is an SS test?
-A pregnancy test.

12:17.200 --> 12:20.360
I thought so.
I am not pregnant though.

12:21.560 --> 12:25.040
Well, put your
legs up here, okay.

12:27.680 --> 12:30.520
Dr.  Willis?
It's what I suspected right?

12:31.280 --> 12:32.760
I need to talk to the father.

12:33.120 --> 12:35.160
He should approve the second operation.

12:35.360 --> 12:36.920
-I want to come with you.
-You don't have to.

12:37.040 --> 12:38.880
I want this. I have to.

12:40.640 --> 12:41.760
Let's go.

12:42.160 --> 12:43.480
And don't get emotional.

12:43.880 --> 12:45.600
It's their right, not yours.

12:46.160 --> 12:50.280
Mr. Paxton, we know
you go through a lot

12:51.000 --> 12:52.680
but we need your approval.

12:54.240 --> 12:57.040
You want my permission
to cut off his leg?

12:58.680 --> 13:00.920
He played in the
selection as a freshman,

13:01.320 --> 13:04.320
he scored more goals than
anyone else in school history.

13:04.440 --> 13:06.000
-He can live normally.
-You don't understand.

13:06.120 --> 13:07.440
This is not a normal boy.

13:07.880 --> 13:11.840
He has strength, balance
and is incredibly agile.

13:11.960 --> 13:13.120
He wants to take part in the Olympics.

13:13.240 --> 13:15.640
Keeping the leg will
lead to a serious infection

13:15.920 --> 13:17.160
which can be life-threatening.

13:19.080 --> 13:20.840
He would rather die

13:21.960 --> 13:23.480
than to do what
you ask him to do.

13:27.400 --> 13:28.800
We don't ask him.

13:29.640 --> 13:32.840
We tell you that doing nothing
will have grave consequences.

13:43.520 --> 13:46.400
Sally, do that again.
It's time.

13:46.840 --> 13:48.680
Embouchure.  Embouchure.

13:48.800 --> 13:50.560
Sorry, I don't speak French.

13:51.600 --> 13:53.080
-Sally...
-Hold him, okay?

13:53.200 --> 13:54.800
Sally, do that again.  Sally.

13:54.920 --> 13:57.240
-Sir, what's your name?
-Surname?

13:57.360 --> 13:58.800
He doesn't even know
what planet he's on.

13:58.920 --> 14:00.760
-Sally.  I agree.  Sally?
-Who is Sally?

14:00.880 --> 14:02.400
I don't know, but it would
be good if she came.

14:02.520 --> 14:03.720
Mario, can you help us?

14:03.840 --> 14:05.920
I told them that.  I met
you a long time ago, Sally.

14:06.040 --> 14:07.080
Angus, take his arm.

14:08.200 --> 14:10.360
-Noa, put it in!
-I'm trying!

14:10.480 --> 14:11.560
Mario Savetti!

14:11.680 --> 14:12.920
-Sally...
-What is it, Doc?

14:13.080 --> 14:14.040
Mario...

14:14.760 --> 14:15.800
-Sally?
- He's running away.

14:15.920 --> 14:16.880
Grab it.

14:17.000 --> 14:17.960
Hold on to him.

14:19.800 --> 14:20.760
Call the security guards.

14:21.640 --> 14:22.840
I need fixations!

14:23.680 --> 14:24.800
Noa, are you alright?

14:25.320 --> 14:27.240
Is it always like this here?

14:28.120 --> 14:29.680
What are you doing here dad?

14:37.720 --> 14:40.200
