recently rehabilitated...

18:36.440 --> 18:39.320
-Shut up both of you.
-Thank you.

18:39.440 --> 18:42.040
Sorry, I'm just saying that...

18:42.400 --> 18:45.840
Your operation didn't remove
the prostate, it's inflamed.

18:46.040 --> 18:48.080
You will need
antibiotics intravenously.

18:48.840 --> 18:51.400
-Prostate?
-Rose.

18:54.000 --> 18:55.040
Rose, listen...

18:56.080 --> 18:58.680
I still am  I am still me.

18:59.120 --> 19:00.800
-I wanted to tell you, I...
-When?

19:01.080 --> 19:03.040
I was just waiting
for the right moment.

19:03.880 --> 19:06.200
-Could you leave us alone?
-No, it's okay.

19:06.800 --> 19:08.480
-I'm going anyway.
-Rose?

19:13.000 --> 19:14.160
What are you doing?

19:14.400 --> 19:17.360
We scan the abdomen
to rule out other injuries.

19:19.200 --> 19:20.480
When will he get his ITS bed?

19:20.600 --> 19:22.240
Maybe in a few hours.

19:24.800 --> 19:26.280
-What's happening?
-Ventricular tachycardia.

19:26.440 --> 19:27.600
We have to shock him.

19:29.680 --> 19:30.640
The pads, please.

19:33.560 --> 19:34.800
Ready.  And electricity!

19:35.120 --> 19:36.400
Power surge!

19:40.240 --> 19:41.760
Back in sinus rhythm again.

19:41.880 --> 19:43.800
-So will he be back?
-Moment.

19:49.400 --> 19:51.600
Unfortunately, its
ventricular wall hardly moves.

19:51.720 --> 19:53.360
He's in cardiogenic shock.

19:53.480 --> 19:54.840
What does that mean?

19:54.960 --> 19:57.440
The brain trauma put too
much strain on his heart.

19:59.360 --> 20:00.880
He won't make it, will he?

20:06.240 --> 20:08.800
Enter antihypotonic
drugs with a three-lumen

20:08.920 --> 20:10.280
venous catheter, and
order a formal echo.

20:14.360 --> 20:15.640
Do you want us to
call someone for you?

20:15.760 --> 20:16.720
My God...

20:28.320 --> 20:29.360
So where is he

20:30.800 --> 20:31.960
Yes, it is an emergency.

20:32.080 --> 20:34.360
-What's happening?
-He's calling other clinics.

20:35.000 --> 20:36.120
He wants a second opinion.

20:36.840 --> 20:38.840
No, don't put me in the queue.

20:39.880 --> 20:41.000
Smaller...

20:41.880 --> 20:43.520
You have to trust us.

20:44.160 --> 20:45.120
We are your second opinion.

20:47.200 --> 20:48.160
Dad, I don't want him there.

20:50.040 --> 20:51.360
Can i talk to you outside?

20:59.000 --> 21:00.360
You have to stop.

21:00.480 --> 21:01.680
It's not that easy.

21:02.880 --> 21:05.560
The leg will become infectious
and necrotic in a few hours.

21:05.680 --> 21:07.840
A few hours later it
becomes septic and he dies.

21:08.520 --> 21:09.680
Is that easy enough for you?

21:11.600 --> 21:13.160
You must be a father now.

21:14.480 --> 21:16.440
I agree.

21:17.360 --> 21:18.960
But you have to
persuade him to do it.

21:20.400 --> 21:21.680
You are the doctor.

21:23.360 --> 21:25.880
I can't do it.  I can’t.

21:27.560 --> 21:28.920
For the rest of his
life he thinks I'm the

21:29.040 --> 21:32.400
one who advised him
to have an amputation.

21:34.840 --> 21:35.960
You're welcome.

21:44.240 --> 21:45.400
Where is my dad?

21:45.960 --> 21:47.160
I have to talk to you alone.

21:48.360 --> 21:50.560
-I'm busy.
-Hang up.

21:55.000 --> 21:56.440
You don't like to give up, do you?

21:58.120 --> 22:00.120
You probably told the
boys that before every game.

22:00.800 --> 22:02.000
"We never give up."

22:04.040 --> 22:05.240
And you never lost a game.

22:09.720 --> 22:11.480
I'm sorry you lost this, Holden.

22:13.200 --> 22:14.320
It's over.

22:16.800 --> 22:18.080
It's time for a new game.

22:21.040 --> 22:23.200
This is going to be harder
than what you played.

22:24.440 --> 22:27.120
But if you work on it,
you'll get good at it too.

22:27.240 --> 22:31.280
You will still be a hero.
For your team, your father,

22:32.760 --> 22:34.600
for anyone who sees
what a man can do after

22:34.720 --> 22:36.880
the worst happens to
him but he never gives up.

22:39.000 --> 22:42.600
You are their captain.
You have to show them the way.

22:58.520 --> 23:00.920
-How do you feel?
-Oh, this is going to be great.

23:01.640 --> 23:02.800
How are you dad

23:04.640 --> 23:06.560
Get it in and prepare it.

23:11.400 --> 23:13.840
Why was there the delay
in the boy's first operation?

23:13.960 --> 23:15.800
The arterial injury did
not show up until later.

23:15.920 --> 23:16.880
How could that happen?

23:17.000 --> 23:17.960
Did the Doppler
not show anything?

23:18.080 --> 23:20.120
